<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3223] SearchWithSortTask ignores sorting by Doc</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3223</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;During my work in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3912&quot; title=&quot;Improved the checked-in tiny line file docs&quot;&gt;LUCENE-3912&lt;/a&gt;, I found the following code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (field.equals(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;doc&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)) {
    sortField0 = SortField.FIELD_DOC;
} &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (field.equals(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;score&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)) {
    sortField0 = SortField.FIELD_SCORE;
} ...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means the setting of SortField.FIELD_DOC is ignored.  While I don&apos;t know much about this code, this seems like a valid setting and obviously just a bug.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
